rule.description:
When concatenating 3 or more strings where all strings except the last end with the same
      non-empty sequence of characters, use String.join() with the following format:

      String.join(new List{
          'line1',
          'line2',
          'line3'
      }, '\n');

      The second argument to String.join() should be the repeating separator pattern (not an
empty string).
